Exercise 2:

Draw the UML diagram of the following class:
public class Employee { 
	String name; 
	double salary; 
	
	public Employee() { 
	} 

	public double getSalary() {
 		return this.salary;
	} 

	public String getName() {
		return this.name; 
	} 
} 



Exercise 3:
Write a program to print the area of a rectangle by creating a class named “Rectangle” 
with constructor having the two sides (width and height) as its parameters
Test the class by creating a main class which contains the main method 🡪 name the class “TestRectangle” 
Use the Scanner library to take the two sides as inputs from the console. 


